               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440819-name-1178" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1178" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1178" type="surname" value="CARTWRIGHT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1178" type="given" value="GEORGIANA"></interp>GEORGIANA CARTWRIGHT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Robert Cartwright, and live in Hereford-street, Somers-town. The prisoner slept in the same room as my brother William Frederick Cartwright—about ten o'clock on Wednesday morning, the 21st of Aug., I noticed as he went out that he was very bulky about the body—I heard him lock his bed-room door—I thought it was very strange, as he did not usually do it—I went to the room after he was gone and missed my brother's trowsers off the chair back—I had seen them there the evening before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440819-name-1179" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1179" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1179" type="surname" value="HARDY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440819-name-1179" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HARDY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable S</hi> 205.) About ten o'clock in the morn<lb></lb>ing of the 21st of Aug. I heard of this robbery—I found the prisoner about nine at night, in the water-closet at his lodging—Mrs. Cartwright gave him in charge—he said he knew nothing about it—I found the duplicate of these trowsers on him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440819-name-1180" type="witnessName">
